In the interview that follows, he discusses how neoliberal capitalism itself is behind the U.S.’s failed response to the pandemic.
On December 31, China informed the World Health Organization (WHO) of the spread of pneumonia-like symptoms with unknown etiology.
The U.S.’s privatized for-profit health care system had long been an international scandal, with twice the per capita expenses of other developed societies and some of the worst outcomes.
To begin with, for a long time, polls have shown favorable attitudes toward universal health care, sometimes very strong support.
This shift to single payer health care would provide the greatest relief to lower-income households.